Here's the `c-avatar` component with RDFa annotations and size variants via `data-state`.

## HTML

```html
<div
  class="c-avatar"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Displays a user profile image with fallback initials"
  data-state="medium"
>
  <img
    class="c-avatar__image"
    src="https://i.pravatar.cc/150?img=3"
    alt="User avatar"
    property="mcs:hasPart" resource="#avatar-image"
    data-mcs-interaction-type="hover"
    data-mcs-consequence="Displays tooltip with user name"
  />
  <span
    class="c-avatar__initials"
    property="mcs:hasPart" resource="#avatar-initials"
    aria-hidden="true"
  >
    JD
  </span>
</div>
```

## CSS

```css
/* =============================================
   c-avatar — Atom
   Displays user profile image with fallback initials
   ============================================= */

.c-avatar {
  /* Root: no margin (Golden Rule) */
  position: relative;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  overflow: hidden;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: var(--color-brand-500);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  user-select: none;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* --- Size variants via data-state --- */

.c-avatar[data-state="small"] {
  width: var(--space-8);
  height: var(--space-8);
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
}

.c-avatar[data-state="medium"] {
  width: var(--space-12);
  height: var(--space-12);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
}

.c-avatar[data-state="large"] {
  width: var(--space-16);
  height: var(--space-16);
  font-size: var(--font-size-heading);
}

/* --- Image --- */

.c-avatar__image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  display: block;
}

/* Hide image when it fails to load */
.c-avatar__image[data-state="error"] {
  display: none;
}

/* --- Initials fallback --- */

.c-avatar__initials {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  pointer-events: none;
}

/* Hide initials when image is present and loaded */
.c-avatar__image:not([data-state="error"]) ~ .c-avatar__initials {
  display: none;
}
```

## Explanation of Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **No margin on root** | Follows the Golden Rule — spacing is delegated to layout classes (`l-stack`, `l-cluster`) |
| **`data-state` for size** | Uses the MCSS state convention instead of modifier classes (`c-avatar--small`). This keeps the component aligned with the framework's state management pattern. |
| **`border-radius-full`** | Uses the design token for a perfect circle, avoiding magic numbers. |
| **`flex-shrink: 0`** | Prevents the avatar from being compressed in flex layouts (common in user lists or comment threads). |
| **Image error handling** | The `data-state="error"` attribute on the image triggers a CSS rule that hides the broken image and reveals the initials fallback. This is a pure CSS solution — no JavaScript required. |
| **`aria-hidden="true"` on initials** | When the image is present, initials are decorative. When the image fails, the initials become visible but are still marked as presentational to avoid duplicate announcements (the parent `alt` text on the image covers the user's identity). |
| **`pointer-events: none` on initials** | Prevents the initials from intercepting clicks/hover intended for the image or parent. |
| **Token-driven values** | All dimensions, colors, typography, and radii reference `var(--token)` — no magic numbers. |

# c-badge Component — Status Indicator

## HTML

```html
<span 
  class="c-badge" 
  typeof="mcs:Component" 
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Status indicator badge with semantic color states"
  data-state="default"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="none"
  data-mcs-consequence="Displays contextual status information"
>
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Status</span>
</span>
```

## CSS

```css
/* ============================================
   Component: c-badge
   Layer: Component (c-*)
   Taxonomy: Atom
   Purpose: Status indicator with semantic colors
   ============================================ */

.c-badge {
  /* Layout: inline-flex for dot + label alignment */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-1);

  /* Sizing */
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);

  /* Typography */
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);

  /* Visual */
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);

  /* No margin — Golden Rule */
}

/* --- Dot Indicator --- */
.c-badge__dot {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* --- Semantic Color States --- */

/* Default / Info */
.c-badge[data-state="default"],
.c-badge[data-state="info"] {
  background-color: var(--color-brand-100);
  color: var(--color-brand-700);
}

.c-badge[data-state="default"] .c-badge__dot,
.c-badge[data-state="info"] .c-badge__dot {
  background-color: var(--color-brand-500);
}

/* Success */
.c-badge[data-state="success"] {
  background-color: var(--color-green-100);
  color: var(--color-green-800);
}

.c-badge[data-state="success"] .c-badge__dot {
  background-color: var(--color-green-500);
}

/* Warning */
.c-badge[data-state="warning"] {
  background-color: var(--color-yellow-100);
  color: var(--color-yellow-800);
}

.c-badge[data-state="warning"] .c-badge__dot {
  background-color: var(--color-yellow-500);
}

/* Error */
.c-badge[data-state="error"] {
  background-color: var(--color-red-100);
  color: var(--color-red-800);
}

.c-badge[data-state="error"] .c-badge__dot {
  background-color: var(--color-red-500);
}

/* --- Variant: Dotless --- */
.c-badge--dotless .c-badge__dot {
  display: none;
}

/* --- Variant: Pill (larger) --- */
.c-badge--pill {
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
}

/* --- Accessibility: Reduced Motion --- */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .c-badge {
    transition: none;
  }
}
```

## Usage Examples

```html
<!-- Success badge -->
<span class="c-badge" data-state="success">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Active</span>
</span>

<!-- Warning badge (dotless variant) -->
<span class="c-badge c-badge--dotless" data-state="warning">
  <span class="c-badge__label">Pending Review</span>
</span>

<!-- Error badge (pill variant) -->
<span class="c-badge c-badge--pill" data-state="error">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">3 Errors Found</span>
</span>

<!-- Info badge -->
<span class="c-badge" data-state="info">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Updated</span>
</span>
```

## Design Decisions

1. **Atom taxonomy**: Badge is a self-contained, single-purpose UI primitive — no composition needed.

2. **Semantic states via `data-state`**: Following MCSS state management rules, all color variants use `data-state` attributes (default/info, success, warning, error). No class modifiers for state.

3. **Dot + label structure**: The `c-badge__dot` element provides a visual indicator that can be toggled via the `--dotless` modifier. The `aria-hidden="true"` ensures the dot is decorative only.

4. **Golden Rule compliance**: No margin on `.c-badge` root — spacing is delegated to layout components (e.g., `l-stack`, `l-cluster`).

5. **Token-driven**: All values reference MCSS design tokens — no magic numbers. Border radius uses `--border-radius-full` for pill shape.

6. **Variants as modifiers**: `--dotless` and `--pill` are class modifiers (not state) because they represent structural variations, not interactive states.

7. **Accessibility**: The badge uses semantic color pairs (background + text) that meet WCAG contrast requirements. The dot is purely decorative (`aria-hidden`).

